fem.components

Class DualZeroDBoundaryCondition

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.model.NamedObject
      • fem.components.DualZeroDBoundaryCondition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDualBoundaryCondition, java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable, INamedObject, IStreamable

    public class DualZeroDBoundaryCondition
extends NamedObject
implements IDualBoundaryCondition
    This class is used for creating dual boundary conditions to be implemented into the model. Boundary conditions are specified as 'zero dimensional' which implies that the boundary condition is specified only at a point (of zero dimension) on the boundary. Any dual boundary conditions specified on an edge must first be converted to a dimensionless stream by hand calculations and then specified as a boundary condition in the model. For example, in stationary heat flow, heat flux on the edge of the body must be converted to a heat stream at several points on the body before it can be implemented at a zero-dimensional boundary condition.
